Tender ravioli are pretty much a win in any form, but they're especially delish when packed with savory tomato and creamy ricotta. Toss them in a delicious cream sauce loaded with zucchini, scallions, and lemon, then give your bowl the crunch treatment with a shower of buttery toasted panko breadcrumbs.

> What's that thumping sound? Oh yes, it's the beating of our pasta-loving hearts!

== Prep ==

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Cover pot with a lid to boil water faster.

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice into half-moons. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Rinse @chopped chicken breast{10%oz} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Toasted Panko ==

Melt @butter{2%tbsp} in a large pan over medium heat.

Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, a pinch of salt, and pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Use pan used for chicken here.

== Cooking Ravioli ==

Once water is boiling, gently add @fresh ricotta & tomato ravioli{9%oz} to pot. Move on to the next step if the water has not boiled yet.

Reduce to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reserve 3/4 cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Gently shake #strainer{} with ravioli in it to remove as much moisture as possible.

== Garlic Cream Sauce ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for panko over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds} more.

Stir in @cream sauce base{4%oz}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, 1/2 cup reserved pasta cooking water, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and juice from half the lemon.

> For 4 servings, use 3/4 cup pasta cooking water, 1/2 tsp sugar, and juice from whole lemon.

== Finish ==

Add drained ravioli to pan with sauce; turn to coat. Simmer until sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted and combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper. If necessary, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until everything is coated in a creamy sauce.

Add chicken to sauce along with ravioli.

Divide ravioli between plates and top with toasted panko. Garnish with scallion greens. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.